[SN]TITLE[SN]
Three injured in 'large scale disturbance' in Glasgow

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Three people were taken to hospital with injuries after what police described as a "large scale disturbance" overnight in Glasgow.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Emergency services were called to the scene in the Lancefield Quay area at about 04:00 on Sunday morning.
One person has been arrested on suspicion of possessing an offensive weapon.
The three people with injuries were taken to the Queen Elizabeth University Hospital, but have since been released.
